{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-template-js","path":"/blog/massivejs-vs-knexjs.html","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>In the field of ORM's for JavaScript there is a dominance of knex.js and Objection.js, don't you think?</p>\n<p>In this thread I have few arguments that convinced me to use Massive.js.</p>\n<h2 id=\"supportet-db\" style=\"position:relative;\">Supportet DB<a href=\"#supportet-db\" aria-label=\"supportet db permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<p>\"Write code once, and then it works with any DB\". It is very alluring promise. But different DBs, not like different flavors of coffee. They can have some unique quirks: types, statements, stored procedure languages, jsonb.</p>\n<p>So tell me any reason why not to use PostgreSQL?</p>\n<h2 id=\"documentation\" style=\"position:relative;\">Documentation<a href=\"#documentation\" aria-label=\"documentation permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<p>knex.js and Objection.js both have extensive docs, many examples. With Massive.js they are a little bit scattered:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://massivejs.org\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">http://massivejs.org</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://massive-js.readthedocs.io\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">http://massive-js.readthedocs.io</a></li>\n<li>search in comments <a href=\"https://gitlab.com/dmfay/massive-js/-/issues\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://gitlab.com/dmfay/massive-js/-/issues</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"api\" style=\"position:relative;\">API<a href=\"#api\" aria-label=\"api permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<p>Personally I feel Massive.js fits nicely into my JavaScript code, whereas knex.js heavily uses Java-style chains.</p>\n<h2 id=\"table-creation-and-migrations\" style=\"position:relative;\">Table creation and migrations<a href=\"#table-creation-and-migrations\" aria-label=\"table creation and migrations permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<p>Do not use ORM for this purpose. This is another huge topic about automatic database migration with CI/CD, and the answer is out there.</p>\n<h2 id=\"bonus\" style=\"position:relative;\">Bonus<a href=\"#bonus\" aria-label=\"bonus permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<p>Do you like blazing fast prototyping with MongoDB? So do I. But do you know that Massive.js provides similar interface while it's still working with PostgreSQL under the hood? Check out section \"Working with documents\" in the docs.</p>","excerpt":"In the field of ORM's for JavaScript there is a dominance of knex.js and Objection.js, don't you think? In this thread I have few arguments…","tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#supportet-db\">Supportet DB</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#documentation\">Documentation</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#api\">API</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#table-creation-and-migrations\">Table creation and migrations</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#bonus\">Bonus</a></li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"date":"June 23, 2021","published":"October 14, 2021","lastModified":"October 14, 2021","title":"Massive.js vs knex.js","subtitle":null,"section":null,"draft":null,"developing":null,"buttonText":null,"buttonLink":null,"secondButtonText":null,"secondButtonLink":null,"featuredImage":null}}},"pageContext":{"showLikes":true,"absolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikolasan.github.io/mikolasan.github.io/src/markdown/blog/massivejs-vs-knexjs.md","url":"/blog/massivejs-vs-knexjs","next":{"excerpt":"You will be more productive using better tools. So, what is your IDE and how you are satisfied with it? I will tell you how many tools I…","fileAbsolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikolasan.github.io/mikolasan.github.io/src/markdown/blog/ide-train.md","frontmatter":{"title":"IDE train","date":"2021-06-30T00:00:00.000Z","topic":null,"article":null},"id":"f20e080a-8dd3-5bb9-acef-34fe03b46b5d"},"previous":{"excerpt":"https://github.com/sematext/logagent-js/pull/277 After some old refactoring in  the function  became unused and still in the code, moreover…","fileAbsolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikolasan.github.io/mikolasan.github.io/src/markdown/blog/pull-requests-to-logagent.md","frontmatter":{"title":"My pull request to logagent.js","date":"2021-05-17T00:00:00.000Z","topic":null,"article":null},"id":"201005d6-06f4-5807-8174-4b0b5ec28603"},"recentArticles":[{"excerpt":"When humans create real artificial intelligence, will it need sleep? This was my thought just before I fell asleep. I was thinking about Lex…","fileAbsolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikolasan.github.io/mikolasan.github.io/src/markdown/blog/should-ai-sleep.md","frontmatter":{"title":"Should AI sleep?","date":"2024-09-03T00:00:00.000Z","topic":null,"article":null},"id":"6a224dca-f97f-56c1-b7e3-59f1cc70ecc8"},{"excerpt":"Some time ago I played with setting up Anaconda in VS Code, but this time I want to upgrade Git for Windows and run it from Alacritty…","fileAbsolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikolasan.github.io/mikolasan.github.io/src/markd